5:
Hey there, what are you doing here
all by your lonesome?
6:
It's about to get dark soon. Want me
to help you find your parents?
11:
A ghost ship carrying treasure?
Sounds fishy to me.
15:
But that little girl on the beach told
me it's true, so it has to be!
22:
Just trusting my good ol' treasure
hunting instincts!
25:
So we're just going on a wild goose
chase...
41:
See, what'd I say? Time for some
treasure!
45:
Tread cautiously. We have no idea
what could be lurking around.
49:
How are we supposed to fight a
ghost if we ran into one anyway?
53:
Back in my day, they fell to normal
attacks.
68: They don't seem pleased to see us!
74: Ugh, we're getting nowhere like this!
77:
You can search all you want once
this place is ghost-free!
107:
What are you spacing out for? Grab
the goods and go!
111:
Thanks for the concern, but I think
we're good now.
120:
I'll get this where it needs to go, so
don't worry.
140: We need to get outta here NOW!
146:
*sigh* For a moment, I thought we
were done for...
154:
The only treasure we managed to
snag was that box. What is it exactly?
158: A music box with a picture inside.
172: You're the girl in the picture...
175:
Here you go! One present from a
ghost ship!
178: ...Did any of the ghosts speak to you?
183:
But a sage once told me... Only
people with strong, lingering
emotions stay in our world as spirits.
186:
None of the ghosts needed to say a
word. Your father held out for so
long because he loved you a ton!
193: There, there... Let it all out...
197:
Gramps used to tell me that ghosts
are just fragments of the souls they
used to be. The people we miss are
already gone.
198:
But... it'd still be nice to see my
Grandma again even if she was a
ghost.
202:
Ugh... Anyone else having a hard
time watching the sunset, or is it just
me?
209:
Okay! That's enough sad time for
me!
213:
We've still got plenty of vacation left
to enjoy! So let's enjoy it!
